						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken slab in the Jaina basti.</hi></p>						

						<p>Yādava.</p>						

						<p>In this fragmentary and damaged record the available details of the date are <hi rend="bold">Īśvara, Vais11ākha, śu 3, Sunday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription refers to a Yādava king (name lost) and mentions Kāḷagāvuṇḍa the son of Boppagāvuṇḍa. </p>						

